<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: OCEANSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thieves in Oceanside looted a car while a body was in the back seat, police 
said Tuesday. The body was that of Tom Van Do, 23, a Cal Poly Pomona student 
who had been missing since Nov. 28. Do had been shot in the head. 
</P>
<P>
Do's body was found after officers answered complaints from residents in the 
400 block of Bush Street that a car hadn't been moved in two weeks. But, before 
officers could check the car, they had a priority call. 
</P>
<P>
A short time later residents were alerted when the car's alarm went off. They 
saw Do's body, partly hidden under a pile of clothing in the back seat. 
</P>
<P>
When police returned they found the car's rear license plate and radio had been 
taken. Both had been present when police saw the car earlier. Police speculated 
that thieves may have disturbed the clothing that concealed Do when they looted 
the car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
