<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEFENSE CUTS FORCE 140 LAYOFFS AT TRW'S SAN DIEGO DIVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beginning early next year, 140 employees at TRW's San Diego-based Military 
Electronics &amp; Avionics Division will be laid off because of a drop in 
defense electronics contracts, according to a company spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
Almost 15% of the 950 employees at the division's Carmel Mountain facility and 
10% of the unit's total staff of 1,400 will be affected by the layoff, TRW 
spokesman Tim Dolan said. 
</P>
<P>
He said about 60 local employees received notice of the planned layoff Friday, 
and the rest will receive official notice between Jan. 1 and April 30. No 
layoffs are planned at any of the division's other offices, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Dolan attributed the layoffs "to the cyclical nature of the procurement process 
rather than the defense cutbacks that everyone is focusing on." 
</P>
<P>
"We have a number of critical programs in the demonstration and validation 
phase, and those are winding down in 1989. In 1990, we plan to compete 
vigorously for those full-scale development contracts. 
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately, we have to cycle down pending the award of full-scale 
production contracts, he said." 
</P>
</TEXT>
