<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOLOTOV COCKTAIL BURNS TEEN-AGER IN GANG ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old gang member was listed in fair condition Tuesday after his shirt 
was set ablaze by an exploding Molotov cocktail thrown from a passing car, 
Burbank police said. 
</P>
<P>
The youth was talking on a pay phone at Buena Vista Street and Victory 
Boulevard about 9:30 p.m. Monday when a car with several rival gang members 
pulled up next to him, Sgt. Don Goldberg said. 
</P>
<P>
An argument followed and a passenger leaned out and hurled a Molotov cocktail 
at the victim that exploded in flames, Goldberg said. 
</P>
<P>
A friend of the victim who was inside a nearby convenience store smothered the 
flames with a jacket, Goldberg said. 
</P>
<P>
The youth suffered first- and second-degree burns on his face, upper chest and 
back, said a spokeswoman for Sherman Oaks Community Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The youth admitted to police that he was a gang member, and that the men in the 
car were members of a rival gang, Goldberg said. 
</P>
<P>
No arrests have been made, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
