<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: MOORPARK'S BRADLEY HONORED BY WSC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Players from Moorpark and Valley colleges swept player-of-the-year awards in 
the Western State Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Freddie Bradley, Moorpark's freshman running back, was selected WSC Player of 
the Year in a vote of conference coaches. Bradley was the state's scoring 
leader and the leading rusher in the WSC with 1,266 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Briggs of Moorpark, a sophomore linebacker who had 19 1/2 sacks, was chosen 
Northern Division defensive player of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Valley quarterback Trendell Williams and defensive back Sam Edwards were the 
Southern Division offensive and defensive players of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale and Antelope Valley colleges will take part in the Golden West 
tournament that begins today at Golden West College in Huntington Beach, and 
Moorpark and College of the Canyons will compete in the Mid-State tournament at 
Cuesta College in San Luis Obispo beginning Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale (4-4) will play Cypress (8-0) tonight at 6, and Antelope Valley (7-2) 
will battle San Diego Mesa on Thursday night at 6. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark (6-3), which has won the Mid-State tournament six of the past 11 
years, will face MiraCosta at 2 p.m. Thursday, followed by a game between 
Canyons (3-4) and Palomar at 4. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Wapnick, a former Moorpark College pitcher, was the first player taken 
Monday in Major League Baseball's re-entry draft. 
</P>
<P>
Wapnick, who played in the Toronto Blue Jays organization last season, was 
selected by the Detroit Tigers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
