<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The "bounty war" between Coach Jimmy Johnson of the Dallas Cowboys and Coach 
Buddy Ryan of the Philadelphia Eagles heated up again as the teams prepared for 
Sunday's game at Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson has accused Ryan of placing a $200 bounty on placekicker Luis Zendejas 
and a $500 bounty on quarterback Troy Aikman in a Thanksgiving Day game won by 
the Eagles, 27-0. "And I think the officials will be on top of the game this 
time," Johnson said. 
</P>
