BAILEY NAMED SHOE'S REPLACEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jerry Bailey was elected Monday to fill the unexpired term of retiring Jockeys' 
Guild President Bill Shoemaker at the annual meeting in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
Shoemaker, who is retiring as a jockey in February, served as guild president 
since 1975. Bailey takes over on Feb. 5 and will serve until next year's board 
meeting when members will elect a president to serve a full two-year term. 
</P>
