<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
SADDLEBACK TRUSTEES CHOOSE PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM NEWTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Saddleback Community College District has selected an Anaheim athletic 
director as its board president for 1990, officials announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The seven-member board of trustees met Tuesday evening and cast secret ballots, 
tapping Joan J. Hueter, a Tustin resident who was first elected to the board in 
1985. Hueter has served as vice president and clerk of the board, which 
oversees both Saddleback College and Irvine Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Hueter thanked her colleagues and urged the board to tackle 
challenges facing the district. 
</P>
<P>
"I would like to see the board spearhead the search for a site for a third 
campus in south Orange County," she said. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, Hueter said she would urge the board to increase the number of 
classes offered at the Saddleback campus in Mission Viejo and to add more 
full-time faculty members to that campus as well as the Irvine Valley facility. 
</P>
<P>
Hueter, director of girls' athletics at Katella High School in Anaheim, has 
taught physical education and coached girls' sports there for 20 years. JIM 
NEWTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
