<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERVICES SUNDAY FOR CANCER, BLOOD SPECIALIST DR. PAUL LEWIS ARONSOHN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Memorial services for Dr. Paul Lewis Aronsohn of Corona del Mar will be Sunday 
in the Sculpture Gardens of Newport Harbor Art Museum. 
</P>
<P>
Aronsohn, 47, a blood and cancer specialist at Fountain Valley Regional 
Hospital and Medical Center, died Saturday of lung cancer at Hoag Hospital in 
Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
A native of New York City, Aronsohn was a former director of the intensive care 
unit at Providence Hospital in Southfield, Mich., and a former clinical 
professor at Wayne State University in Detroit. He was a director and founder 
of the Michigan Hodgkin Foundation and a member of the state committee that 
founded Michigan's first hospice center. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Aronsohn moved to Corona del Mar in January, 1982, and practiced medicine 
in Orange County and in the Long Beach area. Survivors include his wife, 
Kristine. 
</P>
<P>
The service will be at 2 p.m. at the museum, 850 San Clemente Drive, Newport 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
In lieu of flowers, donations may be sent to the Paul Lewis Aronsohn Memorial 
Fund, 49 Montecito Drive, Corona del Mar, Calif. 92625. 
</P>
