<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS WILL OPEN APRIL 3 IN SEATTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Angels will open the 1990 season at Seattle on Tuesday night, April 3, and 
entertain the Mariners in their home opener six days later, it was announced 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The Angels will play three games at Seattle and three at Oakland against the 
defending World Series champion Athletics before playing the Mariners in their 
first home game on Monday, April 9, at 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The Angels' first homestand will have three games against the Mariners, four 
against the Minnesota Twins and two against the Athletics. 
</P>
