<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIKE PRINGLE, BLAISE BRYANT NAMED TO AP'S ALL-AMERICAN THIRD TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Running backs Mike Pringle of Cal State Fullerton and Blaise Bryant of Iowa 
State were selected to the Associated Press All-American third team Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Pringle led the nation in all-purpose running and was second to Indiana running 
back Anthony Thompson in rushing, averaging 157 yards a game. 
</P>
<P>
Bryant, who led the nation's community college players in rushing at Golden 
West College last year, finished fourth this season with a 137.8-yard average, 
behind Thompson, Pringle and Florida's Emmitt Smith. 
</P>
<P>
Thompson and Smith were named to the first team, and Penn State's Blair Thomas 
and Texas Tech's James Gray were named to the second team. 
</P>
<P>
Colorado offensive guard Joe Garten, formerly of Valencia High School, was 
named to the first team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
