<P>
TACOMA STARS FIRE HINTON AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TACOMA, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alan Hinton, coach of the Tacoma Stars of the Major Indoor Soccer League, has 
been fired after his team took a 4-7 start on the season. 
</P>
<P>
He was replaced by Keith Weller, assistant coach with the league champion San 
Diego Sockers, the team announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Hinton said he learned Monday of his dismissal. "I thought I had the full 
support of the ownership," he said. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a big shock to me," he said. "I didn't expect this to happen." 
</P>
<P>
It was the second time Hinton has been fired by the Stars. The franchise's 
original ownership group fired him in January, 1988. He was rehired when the 
new ownership group revived the team in the summer of 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Hinton said his assistant coach, Steve Buttle, also has been fired. 
</P>
</TEXT>
