<HEADLINE>
<P>
LSU'S JACKSON BUYS $1-MILLION POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BATON ROUGE, La. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Louisiana State basketball star Chris Jackson said he has purchased a 
$1-million insurance policy to guard against any career-ending injury while in 
college. 
</P>
<P>
"It's with Lloyd's of London," Jackson said. "It's a million-dollar policy that 
insures me 24 hours a day on and off the court." 
</P>
<P>
The sophomore scoring sensation said Tuesday that the policy is paid for with a 
loan that will be repaid when he gets to the professional league. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson, who set an NCAA record 30.2 scoring average as a freshman, said he 
plans to remain at LSU the full four years. 
</P>
<P>
After four games this season, the point guard has averaged 31.5 points while 
bothered with an ankle injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
